reviews.title: Yup
reviews.review_text: In a world full of overpromises and underdelivering, this little gem just… works. No drama, no surprises, no assembly that requires a PhD. I ordered it. It came. It did the thing it was supposed to do. And honestly? That kind of reliability is beautiful. If you're looking for excitement, go skydiving. If you want a solid product that does its job and minds its business—this is it.
I used this in a braided leather lanyard for an accent. Worked great. Color is true to picture and chord is pliable but strong.

reviews.title: Great for props
reviews.review_text: I used this for a handle on a prop wooden sword for a costume and it worked great. they Cord was strong enough to be stretched a little to ensure it was wrapped tightly around the handle. It added great feel and a nice detail for the piece.

This worked well for making bracelets with pony beads, though the cord doesn't hold up to hard pulling (especially for children tying knots). In a class of 25, we had a few pieces that got ripped or broken.
It did the job. Will take some time to soften up. Do like the product for the simple things I needed for.
this suede cord is nice it's a good color there's a lot of it but just FYI it is a little stiff
It is exactly like the picture. It does feel a little dry

reviews.title: Good experience, !
reviews.review_text: To be honest, I ordered the wrong millimeter whip. However, it was shipped fast and it was packaged well and if I ever need 75 feet of leather cord, I have it.!

reviews.title: Devastated
reviews.review_text: Upon first inspection it seemed like it had durability. I braided 3 strands to create a “chain” to hold my homemade wooden whistles which weigh practically nothing. The slightest tension or tug and all three strands just pulled apart. I'm a small business owner just starting out and I will not be wasting 10$ on this product again. Lesson learned. Embarrassing in fact.
Old supply, brittle, Sliced and defective, of no use.
it was what i needed and worked very well. easy to thread for small hands

reviews.title: Nice Jewelry Cord!
reviews.review_text: Nice jewelry cord! Leather is a great alternative for a person in our family who has sensitivities to metals, elastic, and nylon!

reviews.title: ok
reviews.review_text: color was perfect however was very thin and brittle in places.
Worked out great for the square knot bracelet. My son loved it!

reviews.title: This product exceeds the description!
reviews.review_text: Love this product! Great for adding beads and gems! Easy to use! Will buy in other colors!

reviews.title: Any body feel like a fool for buying this stuff?
reviews.review_text: 1. It breaks (easily) 2. It bleeds/fades. 3. It melts when heat is applied. Long story short... Should've ordered this off of a 2 day shipping website (wink wink). Might have been a better purchase than this spool of crap I can't use!

reviews.title: -1star
reviews.review_text: Horrible. Thin. Itchy. Does not straighten out. Tried several methods. Finally returned. Still waiting on refund as I had cut a strip to use. It was unusable. Waste of time. Tired of all this crap Walmart and A are selling.

reviews.title: Cousin Leather Cord Spool, Brown, 25 yd
reviews.review_text: The Cousin brand is a brand I trust! The color of this brown leather is gorgeous! I have already made a necklace using it! I LOVE everything about this purchase!

reviews.title: Time will tell.
reviews.review_text: This product is ok. I used it to make braided cord to hang artwork up. It's not as supple as I thought it would be but maybe it will last longer because of that. Time will tell.

reviews.title: Good quality leather
reviews.review_text: This leather cord is high quality. This is the 4th roll I've bought and they are good all the way through.

reviews.title: Terrible waste of money.
reviews.review_text: Awful. Has small cuts every here and there. This causes the cord to break if pulled making it unusable and useless. Impossible to complete project.

reviews.title: Cheap
reviews.review_text: Super flimsy stuff, save your money and go to a craft store. Snaps with the slightest pressure, tried to used for a handle wrap and turned out to be a waste of time and money

reviews.title: disappointing
reviews.review_text: Price was okay but when stringing a bead the black paint or dye flaked off.

reviews.title: Inconsistent diameter 1.58mm to 2.94mm on spool
reviews.review_text: This cord is ok - hard and stiff but ok. The problem is that it is wildly inconsistent in the diameter. The picture I took is from 1 piece that I cut to 18". One end is 1.98mm and the other end is 2.94mm! Further into the spool it gets down to 1.58mm. I was in a bind when I bought this from Walmart. My supplier sent me the wrong size so I was scrambling to find something locally. I would not recommend buying this brand of cord if you have fixed sized ends that you are putting it into.

reviews.title: uncomfortable against the skin
reviews.review_text: I bought two spools, brown and black. Looks good, but I believe it is faux suede, not leather, and have no idea what it is made of. Very uncomfortable against the skin. Too bad, as Walmart sells it in the jewelry craft section. Possibly useful for making clothes or shoe laces. Terrible for jewelry.

reviews.title: Strong, supple with texture.
reviews.review_text: I'm new to suede and leather cord. Walmart's suede cord is a great product and I'm anxious to try some new ways of using it. My first project with this product is a necklace. The cord is thick but supple with lots of texture, and feels quite strong.

I really needed this for the crafts im doing and so i put in an order. my order came without it and charged me anyway. i still needed it so i went to 3 different stores looking for it. went to walmart just in case the person picking my order overlooked it and yup there it was on the shelf with others. heres where the hickup came in..... its says 25yards as the size online and on the actual product it says 75ft. soooo.... the person picking it couldnt do basic math??? not picking on anyone just wasted alot of my time and money when this is supposed to save me time and money.

reviews.title: Good suede cord
reviews.review_text: I haven't made many pieces with suede card so wasn't sure if I would like it. I really do! It's easy to work with, although it takes some practice. It does shed a bit while working with it but hopefully that's temporary and won't do it while it's worn. You get a great amount for the price. The color is pretty consistent.

reviews.title: Unusable.
reviews.review_text: This is terrible. I bought it to make jewelry. Once I opened it, I only touched a piece and black dye came off on my fingers. I decided I could not make a necklace with it, because it would stain anything it was worn with. I tried to wash the dye out of a piece and see if it would be OK once dry. The amount of black dye that washed out of it just with water was unbelievable. Plus, it's very coarse and would feel uncomfortable against the skin. This is unusable.

reviews.title: NIce Quality Suede Cord
reviews.review_text: Nice, thick suede. Does shed some. Good quality. Used for making knotting bracelets. Easy to work with, though I do prefer faux products for animal reasons.

reviews.title: Love the Light Brown Suede Cord
reviews.review_text: I love using this particular color in cords because it goes with either silver or gold wire. I have the 75 ft spool. Great price. Will start another necklace with it soon. Using up some of Cousin DIY's faux brown suede cord first.
the cord had a shiny fake look to it because of all the wax on it. cuts horrible. feels fake. you can tell a mile away.

reviews.title: Great Color!
reviews.review_text: I like the color and the quality of this cord. I plan on using it to make bracelets, I think it will look great! I would buy again.

reviews.title: Great for boho jewelry making
reviews.review_text: Great to make an ethnic pendant necklace! I purchased this cord at Walmart to make a pendant with the rocks my daughter finds in our nature walks!
